history.content: It depends. How hard is your humanities class? I would definitely at least keep the other three: EE16A and Math 54 complement eachother well and CS61B is a must just like CS61A is fall semester. You will probably have enough time to pick up the humanities classes later, that is true. Personally, I think you can do it.

children.subject: I took the same classes in spring of freshman year and did fine (I P/NP my AC class, Music 26AC)

history.content: If you are EECS, you do have the option to P/NP your humanities course. However, that sounds like a very heavy load! 3 techs is a lot but also 20 hours is a ton.

children.subject: Why not drop one of the techs? I took EE16A much after Math 54 and it was fine. 3 techs can definitely be a lot to handle.

history.content:
Hi, I'm currently enrolled in Math 54, EE16A, CS61B and ASAMST 132AC. I find myself with little time to actually do anything, and was considering dropping my ASAMST course, especially because I know 61B and 16A will be ramping up very fast and very soon. 

I have some concerns about dropping/ putting off my humanities courses though; I'm a little worried that by I won't be able to enroll in a humanities class that I am interested in because I will have to Phase 1 my CS/EE upper divs later down the line. Also, I'm looking at my 4 year plan and it appears that I will have time to complete these humanities classes later, but I know a lot of unexpected things come up, so should I stick with the humanities class or not?

tl;dr currently struggling with workload, is it wise to drop my humanities class and to complete humanities classes later in general?
history.subject: Course load difficulty and putting off humanities courses?
